00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:07,740
Shaun, you can't just have them stand there while you eat.

296
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:10,240
Part of being a good boss is being a good host.

297
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,370
You need to introduce them to people.

298
00:11:14,330 --> 00:11:16,450
Like me. Right now.

299
00:11:18,420 --> 00:11:20,120
Come here, please.

300
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:24,630
Dr. Allen, Dr. Lundberg, Dr. Guerin,

301
00:11:24,630 --> 00:11:25,710
this is my girlfriend, Lea.

302
00:11:25,710 --> 00:11:27,880
She runs the IT department now.

303
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:28,470
Okay.

304
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:31,010
Nice to meet you all. Please join us.

305
00:11:31,010 --> 00:11:33,470
Shaun's been telling me all about you.

306
00:11:33,970 --> 00:11:36,390
N... no. I haven't.

307
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:39,980
So, I hope Shaun's not being too hard on you.

308
00:11:39,980 --> 00:11:41,520
No, he's been great.

309
00:11:41,730 --> 00:11:44,150
And the case we're observing is really interesting.

310
00:11:44,150 --> 00:11:47,440
We're correcting a 17-year-old girl's tuberous breasts

311
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,110
with saline implants.

312
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:51,740
Dr. Allen told Dr. Andrews it was unethical.

313
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:52,740
He got mad.

314
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:56,410
I didn't say it was unethical. I just...

315
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:59,500
I suppose I shouldn't have interfered.

316
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:02,830
Well, I don't know what a tuberous breast is,

317
00:12:02,830 --> 00:12:05,750
but I think implants are way overrated.

318
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:09,340
That's because your breasts are excellent.

319
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:11,090
Thank you.

320
00:12:11,130 --> 00:12:13,300
That's exactly my point.

321
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:14,800
Mine aren't huge,

322
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,220
but every guy who's ever seen them up close and personal

323
00:12:17,220 --> 00:12:18,930
has been thrilled.

324
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,440
I definitely was.

325
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:24,980
I am thrilled by every part of your body.

326
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:29,740
Sorry. My bad. Total TMI.

327
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:32,610
I'm not even bothered by your adenoidal voice.

328
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:35,030
Except when you talk to your mom on the phone.

329
00:12:35,030 --> 00:12:37,280
But I just put on headphones.

330
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:45,670
At least you'll know he'll be a totally honest boss.

331
00:12:51,380 --> 00:12:53,220
The incision's extended superiorly

332
00:12:53,220 --> 00:12:54,430
to meet the atriotomy,

333
00:12:54,430 --> 00:12:57,600
- and then the inter-atrial septum is opened up. - Retractor.

334
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:01,100
A Carpentier retractor is used to visualize the mitral valve.

335
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,020
That will allow a clear view of the tumor.

336
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:04,310
Can we turn the channel?

337
00:13:04,310 --> 00:13:06,400
Color commentary's getting a bit annoying.

338
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,820
With the right atrium opened obliq...

339
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:13,530
How's Team Browne? Any early standouts?

340
00:13:13,530 --> 00:13:15,860
Jackson's a bit timid, but smart.

341
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:18,240
Wolke is definitely enthusiastic.

342
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:21,660
And your star recruit is...

343
00:13:22,330 --> 00:13:24,580
pretty full of himself.

344
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:26,710
I'm looking for surgeons, and according to his recs,

345
00:13:26,710 --> 00:13:29,380
he can dissect and suture like a pro.

346
00:13:29,380 --> 00:13:31,460
I thought you were also looking for our input.

347
00:13:31,460 --> 00:13:34,010
He's ranked first by every top program.

348
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:36,590
You really think they're all wrong and you're right?

349
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:41,100
So, what brings you all to the biz?

350
00:13:41,140 --> 00:13:43,600
Had my ACL reconstructed in high school,

351
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,850
both my rotators in college.

352
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:48,020
I love the idea of fixing people,

353
00:13:48,020 --> 00:13:50,820
helping them be the best they can be.

354
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:54,070
Surgeons are the ones with the God complex, right?

355
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:57,610
I have that.

356
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:01,660
I spent my life speaking Yiddish and studying the Talmud,

357
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:03,660
and not shaving the sides of my hair,

358
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:06,370
because someone up there supposedly cares.

359
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:08,630
Uh, but then I realized

360
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,460
no one's up there.

361
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:14,090
No one cares.

362
00:14:14,470 --> 00:14:18,800
No benevolent higher power is going to save us, so...

363
00:14:19,970 --> 00:14:21,760
we have to save each other.

364
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:25,680
Can you top that?

365
00:14:25,690 --> 00:14:27,940
- Definitely not. - Try anyway.

366
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:31,360
You're obviously smart. You've got two degrees from Harvard.

367
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:33,440
My parents are Harvard alums, so...

368
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,570
I'm sure that helped me get in.

369
00:14:34,570 --> 00:14:37,400
You're not gonna get hired by undermining your own...

370
00:14:37,990 --> 00:14:39,740
Something went wrong.

371
00:14:39,870 --> 00:14:41,280
Looks like they nicked a pulmonary artery.

372
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,080
No. If they had, Browne would be suctioning

373
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:45,290
instead of Lim reaching in with her hands.

374
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:51,130
What are they doing now?

375
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:52,630
Nothing.

376
00:14:53,090 --> 00:14:54,170
We can't access the tumor

377
00:14:54,170 --> 00:14:56,720
without compromising his entire cardiac outflow tract.

378
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:59,300
What about going in the way I suggested? The median sternotomy.

379
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:02,100
The tumor's too far back. We need to close him up.

380
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:11,560
Proton beam radiation would be too toxic to the heart.

381
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:13,230
So is immunotherapy.

382
00:15:13,230 --> 00:15:15,280
We can't access the entire tumor surgically,

383
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:18,360
and we can't kill it without killing his heart along with it.

384
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:20,700
What if we cut out the parts we can access

385
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:23,700
and try our luck with chemo on what's left?

386
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:27,200
IV doxorubicin and ifosfamide might slow the growth,

387
00:15:27,210 --> 00:15:28,250
give him a few more months.

388
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:30,870
No, I'm not sending my patient home with just a few extra months.

389
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:32,210
It's better than nothing.

390
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:33,750
What about a transplant?

391
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:34,500
Not an option.

392
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,880
Heart tumors are a contraindication.

393
00:15:37,090 --> 00:15:39,590
What if we transplant his own heart?

394
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,430
If we take it totally out of his chest,

395
00:15:41,430 --> 00:15:43,390
we'd have access to the posterior heart.

396
00:15:43,390 --> 00:15:44,510
We could excise the tumor,

397
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,680
fix the defect it left behind,

398
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:47,600
- and then put it back in. - Cool.

399
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,480
Not cool.

400
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,190
At least with a normal heart transplant,

401
00:15:50,190 --> 00:15:51,850
you'd be getting a healthy heart.

402
00:15:51,860 --> 00:15:54,360
Her idea keeps the risk of removing the heart,

403
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,690
and adds the risk that the heart we'd be putting back in

404
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:58,440
has just been severely compromised

405
00:15:58,440 --> 00:15:59,990
having had a tumor cut out of it.

406
00:15:59,990 --> 00:16:02,160
He's young, and the part of his heart not infiltrated

407
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:03,820
with tumor is strong.

408
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:08,120
Do a cardiac MRA and see

409
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:10,500
if the tumor's infiltrated the coronary arteries.

410
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:12,580
If it hasn't, Morgan's idea could work.

411
00:16:12,580 --> 00:16:14,130
I'll schedule it.

412
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:19,050
Dr. Murphy is dividing the breast parenchyma

413
00:16:19,050 --> 00:16:20,970
into three pedicles.

414
00:16:20,970 --> 00:16:23,140
Anyone know where this technique is derived from?

415
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:25,140
Breast reduction surgery.

416
00:16:25,140 --> 00:16:26,350
That's right.

417
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:29,980
And why would I use a breast reduction technique

418
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:32,230
to make the patient's breasts larger?

419
00:16:32,230 --> 00:16:34,480
The technique frees up the tissue.

420
00:16:34,730 --> 00:16:36,360
You can bring the pedicles together

421
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,400
to make the breasts smaller

422
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:41,490
or spread them out over an implant to make them larger.

423
00:16:42,070 --> 00:16:43,320
Very good.

424
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:45,990
And now I'm going to turn the sound off.

425
00:16:45,990 --> 00:16:47,160
Don't worry. Nothing's wrong.

426
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:50,450
I just wanna talk about you behind your backs for a little bit.

427
00:16:52,290 --> 00:16:54,670
So, first impressions.

428
00:16:54,670 --> 00:16:55,580
Murphy?

429
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:57,880
I like Dr. John Lundberg.

430
00:16:58,250 --> 00:17:00,130
I haven't even heard him speak yet.

431
00:17:00,130 --> 00:17:02,550
He has the highest U.S.M.L.E. Scores.

432
00:17:02,550 --> 00:17:04,430
And that's important to you?

433
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:06,050
Yes.

434
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:09,930
It shows he has a broad knowledge of medicine.

435
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:12,680
What is important to you?

436
00:17:12,690 --> 00:17:13,890
Well, I'm more interested

437
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:14,810
in what they can do

438
00:17:14,810 --> 00:17:15,770
with their knowledge,

439
00:17:15,770 --> 00:17:19,020
which is why, so far, I'm most impressed with Jordan Allen.

440
00:17:19,110 --> 00:17:22,990
No. No, you said she undermined you.

441
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:24,400
Which takes courage

442
00:17:24,410 --> 00:17:27,450
and an assertiveness that will serve her well.

443
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:30,990
Then why did you tell her to stop lecturing you?

444
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,330
It's easier to teach an aggressive resident restraint

445
00:17:33,330 --> 00:17:36,120
than a passive one to assert themselves.

446
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:40,460
What about you, Park? What's important to you?

447
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:43,510
I wanna know who I can stand to be around for 80 hours a week.

448
00:17:43,510 --> 00:17:44,840
One thing I learned as a cop,

449
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,220
you don't really know a person

450
00:17:46,220 --> 00:17:48,720
until you've had a few drinks with them.

451
00:17:54,810 --> 00:17:56,600
LAD and circumflex look clean.

452
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,730
What's with the right coronary?

453
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:01,360
It looks narrowed at the origin.

454
00:18:01,530 --> 00:18:03,820
It's a bit narrow, but looks like a normal variant.

455
00:18:03,820 --> 00:18:05,150
Yeah, but it seems hazy,

456
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:08,530
like there could be some tumor infiltration.

457
00:18:09,370 --> 00:18:10,950
What do you guys think?

458
00:18:10,950 --> 00:18:12,290
- Us? - Yeah.

459
00:18:12,290 --> 00:18:13,790
Come take a look.

460
00:18:16,710 --> 00:18:17,210
I guess...

461
00:18:17,210 --> 00:18:19,290
- It's angiogenesis of the left... - Stop.

462
00:18:20,420 --> 00:18:21,880
Interrupting a female coworker

463
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:24,210
is almost as annoying as mansplaining.

464
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:25,470
This isn't a rowing race.

465
00:18:25,470 --> 00:18:27,800
You don't always have to speak first.

466
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:33,140
I... do not love the interruption.

467
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:35,480
But...

468
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:37,810
I like the enthusiasm.

469
00:18:39,150 --> 00:18:40,810
What were you gonna say?

470
00:18:41,770 --> 00:18:44,780
First, um, I'm not sexist.

471
00:18:45,610 --> 00:18:46,950
Of course not.

472
00:18:46,990 --> 00:18:49,110
He's shifting from right to left dominant circulation

473
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,910
to feed blood to the tumor.

474
00:18:50,910 --> 00:18:52,200
- Angiogenesis. - I doubt it.

475
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:52,870
Surgery already showed

476
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:54,540
his tumor extending to the right side, as well.

477
00:18:54,540 --> 00:18:56,160
What were you gonna say?

478
00:18:56,660 --> 00:18:59,290
The pulmonary artery is right behind that vessel.

479
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:03,880
It's causing radiographic scatter in this area.

480
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,800
The haze is just an artifact.

481
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,470
His arteries are clean.

482
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:10,180
I think she's right.

483
00:19:13,510 --> 00:19:15,640
Your idea might just work.

484
00:19:19,730 --> 00:19:21,360
If you invert the sutures

485
00:19:21,360 --> 00:19:22,690
and bury them under the skin,

486
00:19:22,690 --> 00:19:24,520
the scar will be invisible.

487
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:26,940
No one will ever know we were here.

488
00:19:28,820 --> 00:19:30,570
Nice work, both of you.

489
00:19:32,660 --> 00:19:33,870
Her BP's dropping.

490
00:19:33,870 --> 00:19:36,700
Push fluids, start IV pressors. Check for bleeding.

491
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:39,160
She's in V-tach. Move in the crash cart.

492
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:43,000
No bleeding. No hematomas.

493
00:19:43,340 --> 00:19:44,540
Charging.

494
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:47,460
Clear.

495
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:58,520
Sinus rhythm. Her BP is stabilizing.

496
00:20:00,770 --> 00:20:03,560
Get her to the ICU. I want post-op labs,

497
00:20:03,570 --> 00:20:07,150
CTA chest, and full 24-hour cardiac telemetry.

498
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,440
We need to figure out what just happened.

499
00:20:15,490 --> 00:20:16,870
She's stable,

500
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,950
but diffuse delta wave slowing.

501
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:20,830
Minimal brain activity.

502
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,500
An undiagnosed metabolic disorder could've caused

503
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,460
an adverse reaction to the anesthesia.

504
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:27,300
Yeah, but her pre-op labs were all normal.

505
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:29,970
It's gotta be some sort of hidden heart condition.

506
00:20:30,260 --> 00:20:31,300
You're big on opinions.

507
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,930
How are you with ideas?

508
00:20:32,930 --> 00:20:34,680
What would you do next?

509
00:20:36,350 --> 00:20:37,720
I'd check train of fours

510
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:40,480
and reverse the paralytics with neostigmine.

511
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:43,400
If Dr. Murphy's right, she should wake up.

512
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,690
Smart. But risky.

513
00:20:45,690 --> 00:20:47,320
The meds will stress her heart.

514
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:49,990
If Park's right, she could arrest again.

515
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:53,610
I saw a similar case last year. In Borneo.

516
00:20:53,610 --> 00:20:55,570
You interned at a hospital in Borneo?

517
00:20:55,580 --> 00:21:00,040
Uh, no. I, uh, volunteered at an orangutan rescue foundation.

518
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:04,080
Our guide, a local villager, fell out of a tree.

519
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:04,930
It was, like, 80 feet up.

520
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:08,500
How is falling out of a tree similar to a patient arresting

521
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:10,630
during breast reconstruction surgery?

522
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:12,190
Well, he broke his back,

523
00:21:12,190 --> 00:21:13,560
but when we got him to the hospital,

524
00:21:13,570 --> 00:21:15,760
I found he also had heart damage from rheumatic fever

525
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:19,140
and metabolic abnormality from iodine deficiency.

526
00:21:19,430 --> 00:21:21,670
It's rare here, but it's common there.

527
00:21:21,670 --> 00:21:24,030
We only realized it when we ran a nuclear profusion scan

528
00:21:24,030 --> 00:21:25,260
of his entire body.

529
00:21:25,780 --> 00:21:26,810
Good catch.

530
00:21:27,060 --> 00:21:30,400
But a scan that extensive requires multiple radioactive tracers.

531
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,120
You think her heart could handle that?

532
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:33,590
Not tonight.

533
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:35,720
I'll get consent from the mom.

534
00:21:36,450 --> 00:21:37,970
We'll do it first thing in the morning.

535
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:42,090
Once we confirm atrial closure, we'll put the heart back in.

536
00:21:42,090 --> 00:21:44,190
Dr. Lim will reconnect the aorta

537
00:21:44,190 --> 00:21:45,750
and the superior venous connections,

538
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:47,860
while I connect the inferior.

539
00:21:47,860 --> 00:21:49,240
During my sub-internship,

540
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:51,330
I assisted on multiple heart transplants.

541
00:21:51,410 --> 00:21:53,390
Even sutured the atrial cuff in one.

542
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:57,040
I got to scrub in on a liver transplant once.

543
00:21:57,550 --> 00:21:58,700
The... The patient died.

544
00:21:58,700 --> 00:21:59,910
What'd you learn?

545
00:22:00,590 --> 00:22:03,420
That bile duct leaks are a lot harder to detect than bleeds.

546
00:22:03,420 --> 00:22:04,890
Good. Next time, I'd lead with that

547
00:22:04,890 --> 00:22:06,700
instead of the patient's death.

548
00:22:10,340 --> 00:22:11,670
Are you all done yet?

549
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:12,500
Why?

550
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:16,360
Dr. Park wants everyone to join him in the break room.

553
00:22:22,820 --> 00:22:24,040
I'm Alex Park.

554
00:22:24,430 --> 00:22:27,410
I'm a former amateur martial arts competitor

555
00:22:27,410 --> 00:22:30,040
who once thought it'd be fun to spar with a pro boxer

556
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:31,770
visiting my dad's gym.

557
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:35,310
And that guy was, uh, Mike Tyson.

558
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:39,210
Who's Mike Tyson?

559
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:41,700
He's a guy from The Hangover.

560
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:44,200
With the tiger and the tattoo on his face.

561
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:47,960
Nice. You've just revealed you're crazy and old.

562
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:54,240
I've seen the musical Wicked over 50 times.

563
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:57,020
The San Francisco tryout, Broadway, Chicago.

