828
00:37:07,330 --> 00:37:10,780
is a high-risk procedure with a girlfriend.

829
00:37:10,780 --> 00:37:14,730
It's better to show my love than try to explain it.

830
00:37:17,180 --> 00:37:22,920
But I want to be totally honest with you.

831
00:37:29,140 --> 00:37:33,640
I don't like your body because it's excellent.

832
00:37:33,780 --> 00:37:36,000
I like it because it's yours.

833
00:37:38,460 --> 00:37:42,330
And I love hearing you talk.

834
00:37:42,330 --> 00:37:44,220
When I hear your voice,

835
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:47,830
especially when I've had a difficult day,

836
00:37:47,850 --> 00:37:49,490
I find it comforting.

837
00:37:54,890 --> 00:37:57,320
Now I want to hug you. Can I?

838
00:37:58,020 --> 00:37:59,460
I'd like that.

839
00:38:10,370 --> 00:38:11,330
I love you.

840
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:14,220
Thank you.

841
00:38:15,530 --> 00:38:17,770
For your total honesty.

842
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:26,090
Your surgery went well.

843
00:38:26,090 --> 00:38:27,180
With some time in rehab,

844
00:38:27,180 --> 00:38:29,070
you should be back to work in a month.

845
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:30,650
Thank you.

846
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:33,090
Don't thank me. Thank your surgeon.

847
00:38:33,990 --> 00:38:35,740
She did all the important stuff.

848
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:42,900
Lim's golden boy is in. Nothing we can do about that.

849
00:38:42,900 --> 00:38:44,650
So that leaves three openings.

850
00:38:44,720 --> 00:38:47,830
The thought of working with Will Hooper for the next two years...

851
00:38:47,830 --> 00:38:50,030
If Dr. Lim thinks he'll be a good resident,

852
00:38:50,030 --> 00:38:52,030
I'm sure she has good reasons.

853
00:38:52,030 --> 00:38:55,630
She probably thinks arrogance is helpful to a surgeon.

854
00:38:55,630 --> 00:38:57,610
Well, we could try to change her mind.

855
00:38:57,610 --> 00:39:00,110
Eh, she asked us to evaluate the applicants, not her.

856
00:39:00,120 --> 00:39:02,930
She asked us to be totally honest.

857
00:39:02,940 --> 00:39:04,980
Eh, "totally honest" is a relative term

858
00:39:04,990 --> 00:39:07,520
when you're telling your boss she's totally wrong.

859
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:13,370
So, Hooper's in. Who else?

860
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:16,790
Dr. Andrews likes Dr. Jordan Allen.

861
00:39:16,790 --> 00:39:19,520
Oh, I do, too. She's confident, driven.

862
00:39:19,530 --> 00:39:20,880
She won't take a lot of hand-holding,

863
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:23,380
and keeping Andrews happy keeps us happy.

864
00:39:24,050 --> 00:39:26,610
That leaves two more. Who's next?

865
00:39:27,080 --> 00:39:31,320
Asher Wolke is very up-front about who he is.

866
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:33,660
- I like that. - He's definitely eager.

867
00:39:33,890 --> 00:39:35,450
And he couldn't be more open to learning.

868
00:39:35,450 --> 00:39:36,760
Agree.

869
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,380
That leaves one more.

870
00:39:39,590 --> 00:39:41,070
John Lundberg.

871
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:44,060
Smart, professional, mature.

872
00:39:44,060 --> 00:39:45,340
He's a no-brainer.

873
00:39:46,020 --> 00:39:47,380
Lundberg's in.

874
00:39:47,660 --> 00:39:48,800
Lundberg's out.

875
00:39:49,100 --> 00:39:51,160
He stopped by my office before he left.

876
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:53,510
Said he's no longer interested.

877
00:39:54,240 --> 00:39:57,660
He said you all were unprofessional.

878
00:39:58,160 --> 00:40:00,020
Drinking at work.

879
00:40:00,420 --> 00:40:02,700
Asking inappropriate questions.

880
00:40:02,910 --> 00:40:04,190
Dating drama.

881
00:40:07,340 --> 00:40:10,840
So, who's your alt? Olivia Jackson or Boardshorts?

882
00:40:12,150 --> 00:40:15,420
Olivia knows her stuff, but she's a bit insecure.

883
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:18,220
Her answers sound like questions.

884
00:40:18,310 --> 00:40:21,060
I like Boardshorts. He's sensitive.

885
00:40:21,060 --> 00:40:22,250
Like a woman.

886
00:40:27,690 --> 00:40:29,780
I vote for both of them.

887
00:40:30,620 --> 00:40:33,220
That's not an option. We don't have the budget.

888
00:40:35,310 --> 00:40:36,900
Hooper is the worst.

889
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:39,410
The person I said was the best?

890
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:42,950
He is arrogant and obnoxious.

891
00:40:43,070 --> 00:40:45,040
If he works here, we'll hate him,

892
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:48,590
the work will suffer, and we'll either kill patients

893
00:40:48,590 --> 00:40:50,170
or we'll kill him.

894
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,120
And there is no way that you don't see that,

895
00:40:58,120 --> 00:40:59,370
which makes me think...

896
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:03,700
You do.

897
00:41:04,750 --> 00:41:06,260
This was a test.

898
00:41:07,190 --> 00:41:11,230
You just wanted to see if we'd be totally honest.

899
00:41:13,070 --> 00:41:14,040
Well done.

900
00:41:15,250 --> 00:41:17,920
Hooper is definitely the worst.

901
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:20,130
I only let him shadow as a favor to a board member.

902
00:41:20,130 --> 00:41:21,890
I figured I'd give him a second chance

903
00:41:21,890 --> 00:41:23,590
after his obnoxious interview.

904
00:41:24,050 --> 00:41:26,990
And also do a little experiment.

905
00:41:29,230 --> 00:41:30,140
So...

906
00:41:31,150 --> 00:41:35,340
It's Jordan, Asher,

907
00:41:35,550 --> 00:41:38,420
Olivia, and Enrique.

908
00:41:40,850 --> 00:41:43,470
To the next phase of your surgical training.

909
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:44,700
You helped pick them.

910
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:47,310
As senior residents, it's now your job to help train them.

911
00:41:48,190 --> 00:41:50,250
And don't take this responsibility lightly,

912
00:41:50,250 --> 00:41:51,890
because if you don't train them well,

913
00:41:52,540 --> 00:41:53,630
people will die.

